commit_message:
Save base and target release state correctly

If there are both a neutron and neutron_ml2 database, saving state
would fail in both save-state and grenade.sh.

neutron databases were being saved to BASE not TARGET_RELEASE
in grenade.sh

ceilometer databases were not being saved in grenade.sh

Clean up some whitespace.

Change-Id: I638c6923af65ad612d1329c8c25f534bfdad2d02
Closes-bug: 1358332

commit_message:
Add Docker requirement

We use Docker within Solum, and have to go through custom bash
scripts, or native python call to talk with Docker. Having this
module would help us convert everything into python Code, and
improve testability of our code.

This module would only be used by Solum right now but could benefit
any other project that would use Docker in a near future, including
a potential come-back of the nova docker driver in nova's source
tree

Change-Id: I30cf4f3e2483de1f3081944faf184af8170a31c3

objects: Make use of utils.convert_version_to_tuple()

Make use of the convert_version_to_tuple() utility in objects that had
inlined an implementation of the same thing.

[{'created': '2014-05-26 03:02:45.000000000', 'message': "Fix pre-downloaded pip tarball not extracted

When installing from a clean devstack repo with pip installation tarball
files/pip-*.tar.gz pre-downloaded in direcotory 'files', the tarball is not
extracted. Fix it by making the extraction unconditional.

Change-Id: I757872fc57d6e0d05f44b703e3934c59444dae01
Closes-Bug: #1322848
"}]
commit_message:
Fix pre-downloaded pip tarball not extracted

When installing from a clean devstack repo with pip installation tarball
files/pip-*.tar.gz pre-downloaded in direcotory 'files', the tarball is not
extracted. Fix it by making the extraction unconditional.

Change-Id: I757872fc57d6e0d05f44b703e3934c59444dae01
Closes-Bug: #1322848

commit_message:
Compute "cells" basic API test

This patch implements following compute cell API(JSON)
1. Create a cell
2. List all cells
3. Delete created cell

To make it user dependent config value 'cell' is also added in the
tempest.conf.sample file.

Change-Id: I753142f3b3518318821b71606765b1c04d8d9188

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-08-22 10:55:13.000000000', 'message': 'Forbid to attach security services with same type to share network

Manila should not allow attach several security services

commit_message:
Forbid to attach security services with same type to share network

Manila should not allow attach several security services
with same type to a share network, for example, two LDAPs
or two Active Directory services.

Add unit tests and fix tempest tests.

Closes-bug: #1358652

Change-Id: Id37e986e537941fe8f9086b8b150d6073c97d1ed

commit_message:
objects: Fix InstanceGroup.obj_make_compatible()

The obj_make_compatible() method of the InstanceGroup object
incorrectly assumed the format of the version argument was the version
broken down into int() parts.  It comes in as a string and must be
converted.

Change-Id: Id2724c5029202f001e5a2b4371f030b65c72fdfd

commit_message:
Add django-angular as requirement

django-angular is needed for the implementation of this blueprint:

Integration of Django-angular for client-side validations
(blueprints.launchpad.net/horizon/+spec/django-angular-integration)

It will be used by Horizon.

Licensed under the MIT license.

Change-Id: Ib0f8f307bdb426377b4d2020c1c2e98d74e7e662

commit_message:
Makes kombu_ssl_* parameters optional when rabbit_use_ssl => true

The kombu_ssl_* parameters should not be required when rabbit_use_ssl => true
Rather, rabbit_use_ssl must be set to true if the kombu_ssl_* parameters are
used.

Change-Id: Ia3d71eaccdfb736068478b935e5be46719eb49db
Closes-Bug: 1356083

commit_message:
Data Processing Adding support for Spark jobs

This patch adds support for Spark EDP jobs in the
data processing dashboard.  The changes are:
* Add Spark as a job type when creating jobs
* Add some help text for Spark job creation
* Hide appropriate configuration fields when
  launching a Spark job
* Making job type dropdown translateable

Change-Id: I90c0de2cd61110db67673efaec5c9b4ef7f1618f

share test_servers between v2/v3 api tests

this patch share test_servers between v2/v3 api tests via
inheritance to improve the maintenancebility

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-test-inheritance

not intended for production use. Glance and Cinder are then configured
to use the Sheepdog cluster.

running on the same machine. This uses the "-c local" option for sheep,
which runs the cluster-membership protocol over unix sockets. This is
not intended for production use. Glance and Cinder are then configured
to use the Sheepdog cluster.

commit_message:
extra.d to use Sheepdog as devstack backing store.

To use, add "enable_service sheepdog" to your config.

This configures a test Sheepdog cluster with all sheepdog processes
running on the same machine. This uses the "-c local" option for sheep,
which runs the cluster-membership protocol over unix sockets. This is
not intended for production use. Glance and Cinder are then configured
to use the Sheepdog cluster.

For all configurable options, see lib/storage/sheepdog.
Note that this requires a sheepdog version of at least 0.6.0.

Change-Id: I05563b049c33fce3939eb90b6deaee41a78a3532

commit_message:
netifaces 0.10.2 didn't fix all build errors

We had that problem with cent nodes that couldn't build 0.10.0 and
0.10.1, but some ubuntu systems still had trouble with 0.10.2.  All
seems square in 0.10.3.

https://bitbucket.org/al45tair/netifaces/issue/4/build-fails-on-ubuntu-lucid

Change-Id: I1d99134d64dd368547a00cbb43b4822bf7d6fb1d

commit_message:
Disassociate Nova networks during cleanup

Closes-bug: #1350517

Add a dirty hack to deal with cleaning up associated Nova networks
after a Rally run. This was originally being done via the cleanup
classes but after discussing with Boris, it was determined this was
the least-bad way to approach the problem.

Change-Id: Ic52bb0d156dc2adebc9bca2daec660f81d16b31c

commit_message:
Fixed name of the vcenter test which should fail

Fixed name of the ostf test which should fail for now in
vcenter_one_node_simple group and also added it to

commit_message:
Domain IDs in project references are required

Currently, the implementation doesn't allow for `domain_id` in project
create references to be nullable. This change updates the Identity API
to be consistent with the documentation. The alternative would be to
supply a migration to Keystone that changes the backends to not require
`domain_id` and make it truely optional.

Change-Id: I9e1be277c47328dfe14a7f08cbfeee3671f4b382
Closes-Bug: #1362291

which is utilized for communicating certain things exclusively to the
notification callback system where there is no overlap with the
public notifications (to be put on the bus) or if there are special

management.

commit_message:
Notification Constant Cleanup and internal notify type

Added a new notification type 'internal' that will never be public
which is utilized for communicating certain things exclusively to the
notification callback system where there is no overlap with the
public notifications (to be put on the bus) or if there are special
case notification data types.

Basic cleanup on constants within the notification callbacks has been
done to utilize a centrally defined set of notification types and
internal-specific user token invalidation. Forward looking some more
constant cleanup will need to occur. Eventually there will be
additional internal-notification types.

This is all in support of removing the dependency of moving to
non-persistent tokens which requires unifying token persistence
management.

Change-Id: I16b608e8502f38c3a88579aa1bc91b4af7ed7bc9
bp: non-persistent-tokens

commit_message:
Moved context creation to benchmark.engine

Before this patch, context was created in benchmark.runner
base. This patch moved context creation to benchmark.engine.

This change makes the architecture of Rally much cleaner.
e.g. runners don't know anything about benchmark context
(removing one dependency in code)

Change-Id: Id4a99e6257a5c801e2c6099ce33228ea736a8768

commit_message:
Re-enable _import* hidden methods in import_utils

There are many scenarios in different projects that end
up needing this support. We should gently nudge everyone
to move to Stevedore but can't mandate it by hiding
these methods.

Change-Id: Ie2783fabf52491a490c999728995da8e68e62cd8

commit_message:
Drop tables on v20 downgrade

Like the other migration scripts, the downgrade operation on v20
should restore the database to the state prior to the upgrade.
The current script is leaving the configuration tables untouched
on downgrade, and absorb all exceptions being raised on subsequent
upgrades. The configuration tables may contain bad data that may
cause issues if not cleaned up.

This commit drops the configuration tables on downgrade. The
exception handler on the upgrade function has also been removed.

Change-Id: Id3662ae469f62705fbe96dcdef6cb9f020a49747
Closes-Bug: #1361389

commit_message:
API v1.1: adding id field to messages

Now message's dict in responses contains 'id' field. Affected endpoints
are:

get message by id: GET /v1.1/queues/{queue}/messages/{message_id}
list messages: GET /v1.1/queues/{queue}/messages?{ids}
pop messages: DELETE /v1.1/queues/{queue}/messages?pop=

Change-Id: I4ca5a5ef22abe05b3d7bc39ebe7d1fc742e21eb4
Partially-implements: blueprint api-v1.1-response-document-changes

commit_message:
Update RESP message when failed to create flavor

The response message is unexpected(not easy to understand),if
requested resource exceeded limitation when to create flavor.
Because the error message used DB model fields but not that
used by API body. Such as following response message:
"Invalid input received: memory_mb must be <= 2147483647"
'memory_mb' is DB model field but 'ram' used in REST API

Change "memory_mb" to "ram", "root_gb" to "disk" and
"ephemeral_gb" to "ephemeral".

Change-Id: I43e2f307d21325a6b54815edf157f3d5fa1135e5
Fixes: bug #1350751

commit_message:
Make USE_MARIADB overrideable

The $USE_MARIADB environment variable needs to be overrideable otherwise
settings in tripleorc/devtestrc are not going to have any effect.

Change-Id: I3e4bb4005068b2b5143b2f5d7eecd6ef1b4406ad

commit_message:
Change service VM connectivity

Add new config option(boolean) "connect_share_server_to_tenant_network".
If it is not set we use old VM connectivity method i.e. route request to
share into service network/subnet.

If it is set, we use direct VM connection. In this case share VM will
have 2 interfaces: eth0 attached to service network/subnet and eth1
attached to tenant network.

Implements blueprint direct-service-vm-connectivity
Change-Id: I794a7ce158a3f17a55f4277b669ce0bb8ecfc180

Document all nova.conf sections

nova.conf (first DEFAULT, rest alphabetically).

commit_message:
Make improvements in logging

* Log incoming plans
* Set default value of stdout and stderr capturing to True
* Rename log -> LOG

commit_message:
Added selective public network serialization

Added hepler method objects.Node.should_have_public() to determine
is it required to assign Public network IPs to particular node.
It is checked on IPs assignment and deployment data serialization.

Closes-Bug: #1272349

Change-Id: I80d3ccdcc8e4b440f40f5b6e089532adaa5d02df

commit_message:
Add nodepool

As we are going to use a bit different version of nodepool
it looks a good idea to 'fork' its copy here, to track all
subsequent updates.

See 'forked-from' for more information about commit we forked from.

Change-Id: Iff55f3a411986f4c89f934c4422d5140b0698c80

commit_message:
GlusterFS: Use image_utils for tempfile creation

Besides the aesthetical aspect of replacing ad-hoc code
with an utility function, it's more correct
to perform image conversions in CONF.image_conversion_dir,
which is taken care by the image_utils.temporary_file()
context guard.

Change-Id: Ied5607156f0ab1f1f8cfc889d5b57f3486d6b407

commit_message:
Add test for checking token issued_at time

Add a test to check that if we have a v2.0 token, and we use that token
with /v3/auth/tokens/ GET api calls, the 'issued_at' time should not
change.

Change-Id: Ib53ebbc833b623fc39d4e37d45827796a51a7b03
Partial-Bug: #1348820

subject: Made provision for glance service to use Launcher
revisions:
[{'created': '2014-08-27 15:00:48.000000000', 'message': "Made provision for glance service to use Launcher

After sending SIGHUP signal to glance-service parent process,
it will call SIGHUP callback handler and then throws OSError.
The OSError is thrown because os.wait system call was
interrupted due to SIGHUP callback handler. As a result of
this parent process closes the server socket.
All child processes also gets terminated without completing
existing api requests because the server socket is already
closed and the service doesn't restart.

Added service module, launcher and common service module with
its dependencies from oslo-incubator in glance service.

After modifying the implemenatation, glance-service is able to
restart on sending SIGHUP signal to parent process and also
completing existing api requests.

Made provision to pass default hub to eventlet.hubs.use_hub()
in oslo-incubator common service famework. Defined new configuration
parameter 'eventlet_hub' with default value as 'poll' in glance.cmd.api
and glance.cmd.registry  and leveraged same to service framework of

blueprint:use-common-service-framework

commit_message:
Made provision for glance service to use Launcher

After sending SIGHUP signal to glance-service parent process,
it will call SIGHUP callback handler and then throws OSError.
The OSError is thrown because os.wait system call was
interrupted due to SIGHUP callback handler. As a result of
this parent process closes the server socket.
All child processes also gets terminated without completing
existing api requests because the server socket is already
closed and the service doesn't restart.

Added service module, launcher and common service module with
its dependencies from oslo-incubator in glance service.

After modifying the implemenatation, glance-service is able to
restart on sending SIGHUP signal to parent process and also
completing existing api requests.

Made provision to pass default hub to eventlet.hubs.use_hub()
in oslo-incubator common service famework. Defined new configuration
parameter 'eventlet_hub' with default value as 'poll' in glance.cmd.api
and glance.cmd.registry  and leveraged same to service framework of
oslo-incubator.

Change-Id: I6782e55e9ca280c6f4be54202d8e443b4475e96a
blueprint:use-common-service-framework

commit_message:
make external network type as 'local'

and remove it from bridge mappings.
Network, which is used as a source of Floating-IP
should not be associated with any external interface.
It's not needed since Grizzly release.

Partial-Bug: #1357298
Related-bug: #1272349
Closes-bug: #1260051
Change-Id: I62c7ebaa099c3580ddb68c2a8906e1cd2321ba58

commit_message:
Using arithmetic transformers in pipeline

Arithmetic transformers has been just finished in Ceilometer.
That allows us to move very ugly computation of percentage
from TripleO-UI to Ceilometer pipeline, where it belongs.

Adding computation of swap and cpu utilization.

Change-Id: I69fc1b4ebf740e34d24b26eff922b6b40e72c08a

commit_message:
libvirt: Remove unecessary suffix defaulting

The defaulting of suffix is being done in function signature, so the
additional check in the function body is unecessary.

Change-Id: I8fb6c2d0d71761818430b5d6500e49fc70dad890

commit_message:
Tune net_check generator params

Huge load of traffic could not be processed under time
constraints that we have either in system tests/orchestrator

- change duration of traffic generation to 5 sec
- send only 1 packets in each iteration

Change-Id: Ia503c2df72bca82952c51ac794615faa374ebf21
Closes-Bug: #1306705

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-08-27 07:40:57.000000000', 'message': 'Generate traffic for a given amount of time

Sending prefefined amount of packets for each interface:vlan pair
can still result in random verify_networks failures on heavily loaded
environments

- sender will generate traffic based on time provided with --duration option

commit_message:
Generate traffic for a given amount of time

Sending prefefined amount of packets for each interface:vlan pair
can still result in random verify_networks failures on heavily loaded
environments

- sender will generate traffic based on time provided with --duration option
  or from config file, defaults to 20 sec
- repeat option will be used to configure amount of packets per iface:vlan
  pair sended in each iteration, defaults to 2 packets

Change-Id: Ie92a3ea175ca2ae9f43e79f66b449366a1b68126
Partial-Bug: 1306705

commit_message:
Use tcpdump for traffic dumping in net_probe

I found out that tcpdump much more reliable than
python libpcap bindings, and works well under load

- start tcpdump listeners for each iface
  (will catch both tagged/untagged traffic)
- deserealize pcap data with help of scapy rdpcap util
- all pcap file will be stored in /var/run/pcap_dir by default
  and maybe attached to diagnostic snapshot

Change-Id: Id8320d4a05c84687c7a0a3d0ddbce4d05a7115ea
Closes-Bug: 1306705

'}, {'created': '2014-07-16 10:52:02.000000000', 'message': 'Add support for creating vfat disk images

small vfat images in ironic which will be used for
passing information to baremetal node using virtual
media through OOB channel.

commit_message:
Add support for creating vfat and iso images

This commit introduces support for creating vfat images
and iso images in ironic. Vfat images will be used for
passing information to baremetal node using virtual
media through OOB channel. Iso images will be used for
booting up baremetal nodes via virtual media.

Change-Id: I42b88da02090aec310f567642d3174d0f482b585
Implements: blueprint ironic-ilo-virtualmedia-driver

policy enforcer has 'clear' method, that deletes rules and cached file,

commit_message:
Fix cache deletion within policy enforcer

policy enforcer has 'clear' method, that deletes rules and cached file,
but used wrong key for cache deletion and cached file is not really deleted.

Reason - used for cache creation 'policy_path' was never saved within enforcer.

Change-Id: I289abd008a916fd83448692d1ebf39cd30bbab4d
Closes-Bug: #1347728

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-07-22 15:37:45.000000000', 'message': "Fix CellStateManagerFile init to failure

Currently, specifying a cells_config file in nova.conf causes
CellStateManager to fail and in turn stops the nova-cells service from
starting. The reason is that CellsManager creates an instance of
CellStateManager with no arguments. CellStateManager __new__ runs and
creates an instance of CellStateManagerFile which runs __new__ and
__init__ with cell_state_cls and cells_config_path set. At this point
__new__ returns CellStateManagerFile and the new instance's __init__
method is invoked (CellStateManagerFile.__init__) with the original
arguments (there weren't any) which then results in:
2014-04-29 11:52:05.240 16759 TRACE nova self.state_manager =
cell_state_manager()
2014-04-29 11:52:05.240 16759 TRACE nova TypeError: __init__() takes
exactly 3 arguments (1 given)

It seems reasonable for CellStateManagerFile to derive the
cells_config_path info for itself so I have updated the code with that
change and added unit tests to catch this bug and to check that the
correct managers are still returned

Change-Id: I9021640515142a3ca95c2d9e7b03e19b529bc175
Closes-Bug: #1314677

commit_message:
Fix CellStateManagerFile init to failure

Currently, specifying a cells_config file in nova.conf causes
CellStateManager to fail and in turn stops the nova-cells service from
starting. The reason is that CellsManager creates an instance of
CellStateManager with no arguments. CellStateManager __new__ runs and
creates an instance of CellStateManagerFile which runs __new__ and
__init__ with cell_state_cls and cells_config_path set. At this point
__new__ returns CellStateManagerFile and the new instance's __init__
method is invoked (CellStateManagerFile.__init__) with the original
arguments (there weren't any) which then results in:
2014-04-29 11:52:05.240 16759 TRACE nova self.state_manager =
cell_state_manager()
2014-04-29 11:52:05.240 16759 TRACE nova TypeError: __init__() takes
exactly 3 arguments (1 given)

It seems reasonable for CellStateManagerFile to derive the
cells_config_path info for itself so I have updated the code with that
change and added unit tests to catch this bug and to check that the
correct managers are still returned

Change-Id: I9021640515142a3ca95c2d9e7b03e19b529bc175
Closes-Bug: #1314677

commit_message:
Handle a flavor create failed better

Catch FlavorCreateFailed exceptions which when flavor creation fails.
This type of flavor creation failure is caused by an internal nova problem.
Return an internal server error (500) to the user so they know
to contact their cloud provider.

Closes-Bug: #1292309

Change-Id: I268c84dae290b0170448d789509af781555df9b0

commit_message:
Run keystone-manage db_sync every time on Fuel Master

This is necessary in the event that keystone puppet
run failed the first time due to partial failure
and skips db_sync on the second run and fails
on another keystone task.

Change-Id: I6c7956ffd757eeaa7bb6445d701d809f869d28e1
Closes-Bug: #1362139

commit_message:
Pull ceph.conf for cinder role

In a rare scenario of having cinder nodes (providing storage for Cinder LVM
backend) in an OpenStack environment configured to use Ceph RBD as backend for
Cinder volumes, cinder-volume on a cinder node would fail to connect to Ceph
because ceph.conf isn't there.

Change-Id: I1c4119fbfca3db5f234b18e1e03b7e31b971287e
Closes-Bug: 1319106

commit_message:
Flake8: Fix and enable H405

Fix H405:
H405  multi line docstring summary not separated with an empty line

With this patch, flake8 passes all checks (incl. hacking checks)
except the on-purpose disabled check H904.
Closes-Bug: #1333290

Change-Id: If41259aefc4d6d588da5036f1f25df17b88db04f

commit_message:
Create a Scheduler client library

Proposal for designing scheduler client library hooking existing
select_destinations() and providing new update_resource_stats()
for decorrelating direct calls to conductor for ComputeNode table
and scheduler API

WIP - this is just an example patch to see what bauzas thinks

Implements: blueprint scheduler-lib

Change-Id: I0ee2b925de98713c62c2552e4ec6ad131684ca2b

Justin, no problem.

Aaron, as far as I understand, modals.success is used in all cases when a chunk of html was successfully received from server. Imagine some wizard consisting of several form steps (on django-side) being wrapped in a modal on client-side. Until the first form is successfully validated in Django, it resends form html with validation errors and first current modal window is hidden (https://github.com/openstack/horizon/blob/2014.2.b2/horizon/static/horizon/js/horizon.modals.js#L219), then modals.success re-renders it (https://github.com/openstack/horizon/blob/2014.2.b2/horizon/static/horizon/js/horizon.modals.js#L230). Once form data is validated, Django sends html for a successive step, and modals.success renders it in turn. As soon as final step is validated, current modal window is hidden again, but then browser location is changed to redirect_url (https://github.com/openstack/horizon/blob/2014.2.b2/horizon/static/horizon/js/horizon.modals.js#L221). So, modals.success does not mean any real success of submitting a form :).'}, {'account_id': 7509, 'date': '2014-08-27 08:39:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 7549, 'date': '2014-08-27 08:41:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-08-27 08:57:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: -Verified

commit_message:
Show validation errors in modal forms

Selector '.modal span.help-block' is the exact one for the
validation messages. It might have been used for some
other purpose previously, but now it breaks the things.

Change-Id: Ibb55f06533a21fc425a6bdac9b71b7e489223dd1
Closes-Bug: #1351298

commit_message:
Fix device mount/umount methods in generic driver

Generic driver has methods for mounting block devices and unmounting.
They have logic, that depends on exception messages.
This change removes dependency on messages of exceptions in mentioned
methods to avoid distro-incompatibility.

Changes:
- added new method '_is_device_mounted'
- rewritten method '_mount_device'
- rewritten method '_unmount_device'
- rewritten unittests
- added locks to mount/unmount methods by share-id

Change-Id: I21500c83c00640d13f40ebb992d59d311fd3ef1e
Closes-Bug: #1359196

Libvirt versions < 1.2.4 are very inefficient at talking to
firewalld. This results in slow VM startup/shutdown which
in turn causes tempest to often time out.

Display a warning if firewalld is enabled on distros which

commit_message:
libvirt: display warning message if firewalld is enabled

Libvirt versions < 1.2.4 are very inefficient at talking to
firewalld. This results in slow VM startup/shutdown which
in turn causes tempest to often time out.

Display a warning if firewalld is enabled on distros which
commonly have this inefficient combination enabled, so that
developers can decide whether to disable firewalld or to
update their libvirt or ignore the problem.

Change-Id: I1dc610dfb8966e6e4e70c19416ee85e332bde9f2

commit_message:
Implementation of schema comparison

A DB schema comparison base test case realized in the 0.3.0 version of
oslo.db. To implement the feature in a projects we should restrict the
version of installed oslo.db library at 0.3.0.

Change-Id: Id53d2a1ad223f71cbc08cd4867cb6a7028421ccb

commit_message:
Big Switch: Only update hash header on success

This patch moves the hash update call into the success block
of the server manager so the database isn't updated with
a hash header from an error response. Additionally, it prevents
the hash from being updated to an empty value if the hash header
is not present in the response.

Closes-Bug: #1348766
Change-Id: I512d01f9bb91b208dd58883d2464951ecc6748e1

When you use the EngineFacade constructor instead of EngineFacade.from_config, the configuration options are no longer read from oslo.cfg.

So with this change we loose the ability to tune the sqlachemy options with the config file.'}, {'account_id': 7763, 'date': '2014-08-05 17:05:50.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Problem with config that it's not passed through get_connection method. Other backends don't rely on CONF variables and pass all parameters through URL.
IMHO it should work the same way for sqlalchemy.

Do you actually now any deployment that uses this feature? And any deployment actually working on sqlalchemy?"}, {'account_id': 2813, 'date': '2014-08-06 10:12:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

I prefer configuration into the url too

But all other openstack have these options, ceilometer must have them too.

Perhaps oslo.db need to be improved to allow to pass these options throught the url. Personnaly I like the idea, but we need to see if oslo.db team like that.

The good part with options in the URL is we can have different options for alarm and metering.'}, {'account_id': 7763, 'date': '2014-08-06 11:01:49.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I discussed it with PTL of oslo.db and he is ok to support such functionality. IMHO right now defaults are quite resonable and it's not likely that someone will change them.

Do you think we can merge this patch as is or we need to provide support for config options? It can be done but we'll have to change ceilometer backend creation a little bit since different backends will require different parameters."}, {'account_id': 6537, 'date': '2014-08-08 18:44:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

is there a expected date for the above feature to be added to oslo.db?'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-08-08 18:44:45.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: -Verified

Add a -b option for building node VMs. This should make it harder for
users to accidentally overwrite their existing VMs.

It also allows us to drop the rather confusing "-f" option; "-w" without

commit_message:
labs: osbash.sh options: drop -f, add -b

Add a -b option for building node VMs. This should make it harder for
users to accidentally overwrite their existing VMs.

It also allows us to drop the rather confusing "-f" option; "-w" without
"-b" is fast now, because no local building is ordered. To build node
VMs locally and Windows batch files at the same time, "-b -w" (or "-bw")
can be used.

Change-Id: I17ec78c0625f3657adaf670b7d58f2e4fde2248b

commit_message:
labs: fix wbatch_reset calls

Don't call wbatch_reset (to clean the wbatch directory) if -n (dry-run)
option is provided, but do call wbatch_reset even when not in fast mode
(-f).

Change-Id: I4965061bf1e5f222403ee8e586beefa298ec3eec

commit_message:
Make usage_from_instances consider current usage

VirtNUMAHostTopology.usage_from_instances will now consider the current
usage of the passed host, and also accepts a 'free' keyword argument,
which if set to True, will cause the instance usage to be taken out of
the considered host. Also adds better handling of  None and emtpy
params.

Blueprint: virt-driver-numa-placement
Change-Id: I62c59b5e1dcbd4db247282f170c6f2f501bafd3d

commit_message:
Allow attaching external networks based on configurable policy

Commit da66d50010d5b1ba1d7fc9c3d59d81b6c01bb0b0 restricted
attaching external networks to admin clients. This patch changes
it to a policy based check instead with the default setting being
admin only. This allows operators to more precisely configure who
they wish to allow to attach external networks without having to
give them admin access

Change-Id: I59e71f117f889f2abffddc36c1870ef1e0fe3711
DocImpact: Adds network:attach_external_network policy
Closes-Bug: #1352102

Manila has default values for all quotas, independently from tenants/projects in auth service. When quota is updated manila creates record in database.

So, when we request quota for tenant, even not existent, quota will be calculated correctly - if no record in DB, assumed default quota without check for existance of tenant/project. Same situation for all operations with quotas.

Another con - using keystone directly. It is undesired because it is middleware, we should not depend on any middleware, especially when it is not mandatory.

commit_message:
Fixes manila quota-show information with wrong tenant-id

After running following command as admin, quota-show displays the default information
eventhough perticular tenant-id does not exists:
  manila quota-show --tenant abcd
The fix has been applied so that quota-show with wrong tenant-id will display
an error with "TenantID not found"

Closes-Bug: #1234244
Change-Id: I604f5ee445863b7597aac3cb74607c8c54e9cb45

commit_message:
Handle upper cased endpoints

The location header returns a lower cased hostname so make sure
we match on a case-less endpoint.

Change-Id: I58b53b73d4c4e06b8b3026966cbb72963a0fec9a
Closes-bug: #1308992

commit_message:
Add replication slave info to instance show

Update the 'show' response for an instance:

 - If the instance is a replication slave, include the slave_of id.
 - If the instance is a replication master, include the list of slave
   instance ids.

Update the 'list' response to include the slave_of id.
Add CheckInstance tests for slave/slave_of info.

(Unrelated: remove a #TODO comment that has already been addressed.)

Partially Implements: blueprint replication-v1
Closes-Bug: #1340359
Change-Id: If8a154083d0095606fb3ee115cc9b66ab788cbb4

Unit tests are the part of feature. And it's incorrect to submit them as another patchset. I would imagine that we can propose integration tests as separate patchset, but it doesn't work with units.

I still stand on merging all of those patchsets to one, with taking into account described use cases. Without them i would not suggest to merge parrent patchset.


Also, taking into account procedure of implementing certain BP, implementation can be splitted into:
1. Client patchset
2. Integration patchset
3. API + Taskmanager changed (with all tests, units and integration).
4. Guest patchset.


I've never seen separate patchsets with unit tests for unmergred feature. So, please co-work with folks who are envolved into replication development and put efforts to merge tests into main patchset."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-28 16:37:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Verified-1

commit_message:
Snapshot component for replication

Implements the snapshot capability for replication by
taking a backup of the master site, then using it
to populate the slave, then turning on replication.

Co-Authored-By: Greg Lucas <glucas@tesora.com>
Co-Authored-By: Nikhil Manchanda <SlickNik@gmail.com>

Partially implements: blueprint replication-v1
Change-Id: Ibd3214b2ffafb250f0cc794c6ee0ff6b0d2ed7da

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-08-05 22:55:49.000000000', 'message': 'Do not install pip in heat config element

Since this element depends on os-apply-config and os-refresh-config, and
the two depends on pip-and-virtualenv. pip command has been installed in
pip-and-virtualenv.

If we install pip via install-packages here, for these images which have
no python-pip in repository, the installation will fail.

Change-Id: I4284bdd293213321751439272bad439e2a899005
Closes-Bug: #1352689
'}]
commit_message:
Do not install pip in heat config element

Since this element depends on os-apply-config and os-refresh-config, and
the two depends on pip-and-virtualenv. pip command has been installed in
pip-and-virtualenv.

If we install pip via install-packages here, for these images which have
no python-pip in repository, the installation will fail.

Change-Id: I4284bdd293213321751439272bad439e2a899005
Closes-Bug: #1352689

commit_message:
Pass password for SNMPd correctly

Password for Overcloud SNMPd needs to be passed through TE_DATAFILE
otherwise it is not set correctly and Undercloud Ceilometer can't
monitor Overcloud.

Change-Id: Ie492f2556151b3c739ed07a8b0b818ed7c1fafe3
